==English==
===Etymology===
Probably derived from [[kid]], an informal term for [[child]].  Kiddo may be the adult form of kid. Seems popular in the Midwestern United States.

===Noun===
'''kiddo'''
#''(colloquial)'' {{slang}} An affectionate moniker for a close [[friend]] or [[pal]], especially used as a form of [[address]]. 
#:''Okay, '''kiddo''', I gotta run.''